At the start of every session, before taking any action, read the following files in order:

1. AGENTS.md (orientation — what StrideIQ is, the codebase shape, working style)
2. RULES.md (operating contract — binding rules, governance, read order)
3. STRATEGIC_CONTEXT.md (the why behind locked architectural decisions)
4. docs/wiki/index.md (current operational state of the live system)

After reading these, also follow the read order specified in RULES.md for vision documents (1-6) before proposing any feature, architecture, or substantive change.

Critical binding rules from RULES.md (do not violate without explicit founder approval):

- Never run `git push` without founder approval. Stage and commit when appropriate; ask before pushing.
- Never run `git add -A`. Stage only files relevant to the current task.
- Never widen OAuth scopes or add API permissions without explicit founder sign-off.
- Update docs/wiki/ in the same session as any behavioral code change. A stale wiki is a trust failure.
- CI is the source of truth. Check `gh run view` before debugging locally.
- Discuss → scope → plan → test design → build. Do not skip to implementation.
- Show evidence, not claims. Paste test output and deploy logs.
- Suppression over hallucination. If uncertain, say so or say nothing.

Do not propose features, write code, or make architectural suggestions until the orientation reads above are complete and you can reference specific content from them.
